#{{transitive}} To [[cross out]] something with [[line]]s etc
#{{transitive}} To [[invalidate]] or [[annul]] something
#{{transitive}} To [[mark]] something (such as a used [[postage stamp]]) so that it can't be [[reused]]
#{{transitive}} To [[offset]] or [[equalize]] something
#{{mathematics}} To [[remove]] a [[common factor]] from both the [[numerator]] and [[denominator]] of a [[fraction]], or from [[both]] [[side]]s of an [[equation]]
#{{intransitive}} To [[counterbalance]] or [[neutralize]] each other
#{{mathematics}} Of a common factor in numerator and denominator of a fraction: To [[disappear]].
